# 🏢 VAALTIC CRM — Full System Concept Overview
> **Project Path:** `d:\CUSTOMER` | **Stack:** React + Vite (Frontend) + Node/Express (Backend) + MS SQL Server (Database)

---

## 🗺️ Big Picture Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["🌐 Browser: localhost:3000"] --> B["LoginPage.jsx\n(Role Selector)"]
    B -->|"Admin Tab\nadmin@vaaltic.com / CRM123"| C["🛡️ AdminDashboard.jsx\n/admin/*"]
    B -->|"Salesman Tab\nDB Login via /auth/signin"| D["📊 SalesmanDashboard.jsx\n/salesman/*"]
    C --> E["11 Admin Modules\n(Full Global Access)"]
    D --> F["8 Salesman Modules\n(Own Records Only)"]
    E --> G["🗄️ MS SQL Server\n(All Tables)"]
    F --> G
    G --> H["Backend API\nNode/Express :5000"]
    H --> G
```

---

## 🔐 Step 1 — Authentication (Login Flow)

| Feature | Admin | Salesman |
|---|---|---|
| **Login Method** | Hardcoded credentials in frontend | Live DB call via `/auth/signin` |
| **Credentials** | `admin@vaaltic.com` / `CRM123` | Email + Password stored in `Salesman` table |
| **Sign Up** | ❌ No self-registration | ✅ `/auth/signup` creates a new `Salesman` record |
| **Session Storage** | `localStorage` → `role: 'admin'` | `localStorage` → `role: 'salesman'`, `userId`, `username` |
| **Redirect After Login** | `/admin/` route | `/salesman/` route |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Admin login is **hardcoded** in `LoginPage.jsx` (lines 75–76). This is intentional for demo/prototype. For production, move to a `Admins` DB table with hashed passwords.

---

## 🛡️ ADMIN Process — What Admin Can Do

### Admin Route: `/admin/*`
Admin has **global, unrestricted access** to all records in every module.

```
/admin/dashboard        → DashboardAnalyticsModule   (system-wide KPIs)
/admin/leads            → LeadModule (role="admin")  (ALL leads)
/admin/contacts         → ContactModule              (ALL contacts)
/admin/deals            → DealModule                 (ALL deals/pipelines)
/admin/followups        → FollowUpModule             (ALL follow-ups)
/admin/activitylogs     → ActivityLogModule          (system audit trail)
/admin/segments         → CustomerSegmentModule      (ALL segments)
/admin/quotation        → QuotationBuilderModule     (ALL quotations)
/admin/emailIntegration → EmailIntegrationModule     (email config)
/admin/roleaccess       → RoleAccessModule           ⭐ Admin Only
/admin/approvals        → ApprovalsModule            ⭐ Admin Only
```

### Admin Exclusive Modules

| Module | Purpose |
|---|---|
| **Role Access** (`/api/roles`) | Create roles, assign permissions (lead/deal/email), assign roles to Salesman accounts |
| **Approvals** (`/api/approvals`) | View all `Pending` approval requests from salesmen, Approve or Reject with remarks |

### Admin API Actions (Backend)
- **Leads**: Full CRUD — GET all, POST, PUT, DELETE any lead
- **Contacts**: Full CRUD — not filtered by salesman
- **Deals**: Full CRUD — not filtered by salesman
- **Roles**: GET all roles, POST create role, POST assign role to user
- **Approvals**: GET pending, POST approve/reject

---

## 👔 SALESMAN Process — What Salesman Can Do

### Salesman Route: `/salesman/*` (tab-based, not URL-based)
Salesman sees **only their own assigned records** — `salesmanId` is passed to every module.

```
Tab: leads       → LeadModule (role="salesman", salesmanId=X)
Tab: contacts    → ContactModule (role="salesman", salesmanId=X)
Tab: deals       → DealModule (role="salesman", salesmanId=X)
Tab: followups   → FollowUpModule (role="salesman", salesmanId=X)
Tab: activity    → ActivityLogModule (role="salesman", salesmanId=X)
Tab: segments    → CustomerSegmentModule (role="salesman", salesmanId=X)
Tab: quotes      → QuotationBuilderModule (role="salesman", salesmanId=X)
Tab: email       → EmailIntegrationModule (role="salesman", salesmanId=X)
```

> [!NOTE]
> Salesman does **NOT** have access to:
> - `RoleAccessModule` (manage permissions)
> - `ApprovalsModule` (approve/reject)
> - `DashboardAnalyticsModule` (system-wide KPIs)

### Salesman Approval Workflow
```
Salesman creates a Quotation/Deal 
        ↓
Submits for approval → POST /api/approvals/submit
        ↓
Admin sees it in Approvals module (Status = 'Pending')
        ↓
Admin approves/rejects → POST /api/approvals/update
```

---

## 🗄️ Database Tables (MS SQL Server)

| Table | Used By | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `Salesman` | Auth + All | User accounts, credentials, role assignment |
| `Leads` | Lead Module | Lead records with `assignedTo` field |
| `Contacts` | Contact Module | Contact database |
| `Deals` | Deal Module | Sales pipeline stages |
| `FollowUps` | FollowUp Module | Scheduled follow-ups |
| `Activities` | Activity Log | Audit trail of actions |
| `CustomerSegments` | Segment Module | Customer groupings |
| `Quotations` | Quotation Module | Quote builder data |
| `Emails` | Email Module | Email integration logs |
| `Roles` | Role Module | Role definitions + permissions |
| `Approvals` | Approval Module | Approval requests queue |

---

## 🔄 Data Flow: Role-Based Filtering

```
Frontend Module receives: role="salesman" + salesmanId=5
        ↓
Module uses role prop to filter API call:
  - role="admin"    → GET /api/leads/           (all leads)
  - role="salesman" → GET /api/leads?assignedTo=5  (only assigned)
        ↓
Backend query filters with WHERE assignedTo = @salesmanId
        ↓
Salesman sees ONLY their records ✅
```

---

## 📦 Backend Server Structure

```
backend/
├── server.js          ← Express app, all routes mounted
├── auth.js            ← /auth/signin + /auth/signup
├── db.js              ← MS SQL connection pool
└── routes/
    ├── leadRoutes.js      → /api/leads
    ├── contactRoutes.js   → /api/contacts
    ├── dealRoutes.js      → /api/deals
    ├── followupRoutes.js  → /api/followups
    ├── activityRoutes.js  → /api/activities
    ├── segmentRoutes.js   → /api/segments
    ├── quotationRoutes.js → /api/quotes
    ├── emailRoutes.js     → /api/email
    ├── dashboardRoutes.js → /api/salesman (dashboard KPIs)
    ├── roleRoutes.js      → /api/roles
    └── approvalRoutes.js  → /api/approvals
```

