## ⚠️ Known Gaps / Improvement Points

| Issue | Impact | Recommended Fix |
|---|---|---|
| Admin login is hardcoded | Security risk in production | Move to `Admins` DB table with bcrypt hashed passwords |
| No JWT/token auth | Any user can call any API directly | Add JWT middleware to backend routes |
| `leadRoutes.js` GET `/` returns ALL leads | Salesman filter is frontend-only | Add `?assignedTo=` query filter in backend |
| Password stored plain text in `Salesman` table | Security risk | Use `bcrypt` to hash passwords |
| Admin username hardcoded as "Admin User" | Poor personalization | Pull from session/DB |

---

## ✅ What Is Working Correctly

- ✅ Role separation: Admin → `/admin/*`, Salesman → `/salesman/*`
- ✅ `salesmanId` passed from localStorage to all modules
- ✅ Unauthorized salesman cannot access admin URL (redirected to login)
- ✅ Approval workflow: Submit → Pending → Admin approves/rejects
- ✅ Role management: Admin can create roles and assign to salesman
- ✅ 11 backend routes mounted and active on server startup
- ✅ DB health check middleware on every request
- ✅ Shared `Sidebar.jsx` with `role` prop controls which tabs are shown
